<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<worksheet>
  <title>Final Review, Part I</title>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Consider the vectors
<md>
\vvec_1=\threevec2{-1}0, \hspace*{24pt}
\vvec_2=\threevec122, \hspace*{24pt}
\vvec_3=\threevec502, \hspace*{24pt}.
</md></p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What does it mean to say that a vector <m>\bvec</m> is a linear
  combination of the vectors <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, and <m>\vvec_3</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\bvec=\threevec054</m> a linear combination of <m>\vvec_1</m>,
  <m>\vvec_2</m>, and <m>\vvec_3</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>In how many ways can <m>\bvec</m> be
  written as a linear combination of these three vectors?  If more
  than one, demonstrate two ways in which <m>\bvec</m> is a linear
  combination of the vectors.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1.5in">
      <statement>
        <p>Do the vectors <m>\vvec_1</m>, <m>\vvec_2</m>, <m>\vvec_3</m> span <m>\real^3</m>?  If
  not, find a vector that is not in <m>\span{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Give a geometric description of <m>\span{\vvec_1,\vvec_2,\vvec_3}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>A = \begin{bmatrix}\vvec_1 \amp \vvec_2 \amp \vvec_3 \end{bmatrix}</m>,
  write the solution set of the equation <m>A\xvec = \bvec</m> in vector
  parametric form.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Remember that <m>\col(A)</m> is the subspace that is the span of the
  columns of <m>A</m>.  Find a basis for <m>\col(A)</m> and explain why your set
  is a basis.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is the dimension of <m>\col(A)</m> and for which <m>p</m> is
  <m>\col(A)</m> a subspace of <m>\real^p</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Is the matrix <m>A</m> invertible?  Explain your response.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If a vector <m>\bvec</m> is in <m>\col(A)</m>, what can you say about the set
  of solutions to the equation <m>A\xvec = \bvec</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise workspace="1in">
    <introduction>
      <p>We earlier defined the <em>rank</em> of a matrix <m>A</m> to be the
  number of pivot positions in <m>A</m>.  Suppose that <m>A</m> is a <m>3\times4</m>
  matrix.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\rank(A) = 3</m>, what can you say about <m>\col(A)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\rank(A) = 1</m>, what can you say about <m>\col(A)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Give an example of a <m>3\times4</m> matrix <m>A</m> whose rank is <m>1</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <introduction>
      <p>Suppose that <m>A</m> is a <m>10\times15</m> matrix.</p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>What is the largest
  possible value for <m>\rank(A)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\rank(A)</m> is this largest possible value, what can you say about
  <m>\col(A)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>B</m> is a <m>12\times10</m> matrix, what is the largest possible
  value of <m>\rank(B)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>\rank(B)</m> is this largest possible value, what can you say about
  <m>\col(B)</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>If <m>C</m> is a <m>14\times n</m> matrix and <m>\col(C)=\real^{14}</m>, what can
  you conclude about <m>n</m>?</p>
      </statement>
    </task>
  </exercise>

</worksheet>
